AETNA

At this point my plan calls on me to explain the artificer and cause of the fire, a cause of no little or slight significance: it is overwhelming, and will lay before you a thousand truths in a moment of time. Facts and eyes are our teachers‚ facts force belief unassisted. Moreover Ι would suggest to you to handle and touch, if it might safely be done3 but the flames forbid, and there is a fire to keep guard upon Aetna's working which shuts off all approach, since the divine providence which governs creation will have no witness of its action, so to heighten the show, and not relieve the mountain ineffectually. All will be the same, but you are to see it from a distance: none the less it is no matter for doubt what it is that makes Aetna writhe within, or who is the wondrous workman that directs a craft so mighty.
